docs.lead_paragraph: PANAMA, Sept. 1--A resolution calling for expert study of ocean freight and insurance rates in the inter-American trade was adopted over the objections of the United States delegate, Huntington Morse, at a meeting of the special committee of the Inter-American Economic and Social Council held here this week. Only Uruguay and Bolivia voted with the American delegate.

docs.lead_paragraph: It was a quiet and uneventful week in the foreign exchange market. The extended holiday running up to tomorrow (Tuesday) and the fact that end-of-August requirements had been completed earlier, combined to make for light transfers and narrow price changes.
